Reasoning: The paper deals with identifying objects in images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of the M\"obius group and conformal camera model suggests a focus on geometric and graphical representations of shapes and images, which falls under the sub-category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The development of an algorithm for shape recognition and the use of invariants suggests a focus on machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG). The use of numerical stability and robustness to noise suggests a focus on computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of neurological aspects of vision suggests a possible connection to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
